    "That one application is then submitted to the campuses that the students would like to attend, including highly selective, elite campuses (Berkeley, Los Angeles) along with less selective campuses (Riverside, Merced).",
    "Students are therefore unable to tailor their applications to specific campuses.",
    "Applicants have to write essays written to four of eight possible prompts (70 possible combinations).",
    "The essay prompts are similar to those used by the Common App, an independent, national college application platform (see Table A1 for a full list of the prompts).",
    "Our UC data come from every Latinx identifying in-state applicant who applied during the 2016-2017 academic year (well before ChatGPT was released)."
